Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.38,0:01:59.30,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.05,0:02:03.22,dialogue,,0,0,0,,can you sell me something to eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.01,0:02:05.60,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at these crops.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.60,0:02:09.10,dialogue,,0,0,0,,We had a cold summer; we're\Nbarely getting by ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.48,0:02:10.52,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.48,0:02:13.73,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Try the neighboring town.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.44,0:02:17.99,dialogue,,0,0,0,,They've got quite a crop this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.24,0:02:20.86,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yo, don't tell him that stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.28,0:02:24.54,dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'd best avoid it. The rice there isn't normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.95,0:02:27.54,dialogue,,0,0,0,,They get an ample harvest every time there's a disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.71,0:02:29.54,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the ancestors' curse, they say.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.67,0:02:35.05,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a cursed harvest.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.34,0:02:36.46,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a cursed harvest.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.01,0:02:40.59,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The ancestors are going to take someone away again.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.89,0:02:43.35,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who's it going to be this year?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.60,0:02:48.23,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The ancestors always take the weakest one first.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.89,0:02:51.90,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow, those are fine crops.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.32,0:02:57.11,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who are you? What do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.40,0:03:00.28,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was just wondering if you could\Nsell me something to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.66,0:03:08.66,dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's nothing to give to outsiders. We\Ndon't get enough rice to last the year.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.16,0:03:11.96,dialogue,,0,0,0,,We need to stock as much as we can while we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.75,0:03:16.92,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah? So is this year's big crop a miracle?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.21,0:03:18.88,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.67,0:03:25.80,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The ancestors are protecting us through the\Nsoil because we worship them diligently.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.27,0:03:32.35,dialogue,,0,0,0,,And they take one of you in exchange, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.81,0:03:37.65,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seems a bit harsh for something your\Nancestors would do, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.53,0:03:42.91,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.74,0:03:46.74,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see it differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.74,0:03:49.83,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can you tell me a little more about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.54,0:04:01.92,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've been told that it's been this way for a while – every\Ntime there's a disaster, we get a strong harvest.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.72,0:04:09.39,dialogue,,0,0,0,,And every such year, someone would\Ngrow a "divine fang" in their mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.39,0:04:14.14,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The tooth falls out at the end of autumn,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.73,0:04:17.61,dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the person dies.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.15,0:04:27.78,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The life is an offering made to the ancestors.\NThat's what we've all been told.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.58,0:04:31.54,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone's been thankful though.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.08,0:04:38.34,dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it weren't for the miracles, we wouldn't have\Nsurvived until now in this barren land.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.75,0:04:42.67,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do all the lost ones share something in common?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.76,0:04:46.84,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's always the weakest one, I'm told.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.22,0:04:50.51,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The bodies are buried?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.31,0:04:51.81,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.35,0:04:53.43,dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the teeth?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.69,0:05:00.36,notes,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,0)}Saishu: chief mourner
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.69,0:04:57.98,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Saishu-sama enshrines them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.44,0:05:00.36,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The chief mourner?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.52,0:05:03.44,dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's the man who manages all\Nof the festivities in this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.61,0:05:08.87,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've been taught a lot, because I'll be taking his role.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.70,0:05:13.79,dialogue,,0,0,0,,After the teeth fall out, they become\Nvisible only to the Saishu-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.54,0:05:17.37,dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the Saishu-sama enshrines them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.83,0:05:19.46,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are you going to be following his path?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.63,0:05:26.59,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm like the chief mourner; sometimes\NI see things that others can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.01,0:05:31.10,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd like to see that "Saishu".
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.52,0:05:34.64,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saishu-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.44,0:05:37.81,dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's probably in the garden around the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.28,0:05:47.15,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A diary and Agricultural texts.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.41,0:05:50.16,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's been a while since I've had a guest.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.41,0:05:52.95,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who exactly are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.83,0:05:58.83,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm a Mushi-shi, Ginko.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.54,0:06:03.88,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm looking for a "Narazu seed".
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.17,0:06:07.63,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.43,0:06:12.18,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sane, you still have work to do, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.18,0:06:13.85,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come back when you're done.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.47,0:06:18.35,dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've got a big crop this year. We'd better\Nbe ready or we won't be able to keep up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.02,0:06:19.65,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.35,0:06:23.40,dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, are you still worried about your mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.90,0:06:28.53,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.53,0:06:29.49,dialogue,,0,0,0,,She'll be okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.99,0:06:32.12,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here, give her this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.66,0:06:35.16,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.62,0:06:42.00,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've been told that you Mushi-shi folk\Nhave been here in the past as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.25,0:06:48.72,dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you're wasting time. There is no such seed here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.63,0:06:53.93,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, are you saying the crops here\Nare thanks to your ancestors' powers?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.51,0:06:56.10,dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Ancestors' powers", huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.97,0:06:58.43,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Indeed, that's part of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.14,0:07:03.81,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's thanks to everyone's faith that we can\Nall work without abandoning this land.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.07,0:07:06.48,dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that's not all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.24,0:07:11.82,dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've spent countless years studying\Nways to fertilize the soil.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.53,0:07:16.33,dialogue,,0,0,0,,At times, that effort brings us results like this year's.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.95,0:07:18.83,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our harvest is growing each year as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.62,0:07:22.04,dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, about the "divine fang".
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.96,0:07:29.92,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not impossible for a grown man to grow a tooth.\NThat's got nothing to do with the harvest.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.22,0:07:31.72,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, leave please.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.13,0:07:33.97,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let me ask one more thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.97,0:07:36.81,dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.68,0:07:40.10,dialogue,,0,0,0,,You seem to know about the "Narazu seed".
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.48,0:07:43.90,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I've heard about it from my elders.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.52,0:07:50.74,notes,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,0)}Koumyaku: stream of light
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.52,0:07:50.74,dialogue,,0,0,0,,That a Mushi-shi contained a\N"Koumyaku" in it – or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.86,0:07:51.49,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.32,0:07:54.70,dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can sense the "Koumyaku" yourself, can't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.78,0:07:57.74,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Being that you can see Mushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.25,0:08:03.87,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The weaker a Mushi is, the more\Nlight they expose themselves to,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.67,0:08:07.38,dialogue,,0,0,0,,because they're close to the Kouki, the root of all Mushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.00,0:08:10.34,dialogue,,0,0,0,,A Koumyaku is a channel in which Kouki flows.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.63,0:08:13.97,dialogue,,0,0,0,,In a sense, it is life itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.43,0:08:18.43,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Manipulated correctly, it can be used for anything – even immortality or resurrection.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.39,0:08:23.39,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, such an action is highly taboo to us Mushi-shi.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.27,0:08:27.15,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yet, countless exceptions exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.36,0:08:29.90,dialogue,,0,0,0,,That seed is one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.53,0:08:34.70,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Buried in soil, it'll yield fertility in the area for a year,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.36,0:08:38.83,dialogue,,0,0,0,,and a being will be stolen of its life as compensation.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.58,0:08:43.21,dialogue,,0,0,0,,That is the record that has been passed down to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.50,0:08:47.71,dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, what do you plan to do with it when you find it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.25,0:08:51.21,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Destroy it? Use it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.55,0:08:54.30,dialogue,,0,0,0,,That happens to be what I want to ask as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.93,0:09:02.10,dialogue,,0,0,0,,What would you do if you could save many\Nlives at the expense of one life?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.77,0:09:05.06,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.44,0:09:12.11,dialogue,,0,0,0,,If such a seed exists, it'd be a sin\Nto let such an opportunity go.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.78,0:09:20.08,dialogue,,0,0,0,,But to bury it with the knowledge that someone\Nwill surely die is tantamount to murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.16,0:09:26.87,dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter how many lives are saved as a result,\None life is taken away regardless of their will.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.42,0:09:33.59,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyone would surely dirty their hands with such a crime,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.59,0:09:36.59,dialogue,,0,0,0,,if one person's sacrifice could save two lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.13,0:09:41.64,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Naturally, in the short term it's difficult not to use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.14,0:09:45.23,dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you use it once, you'll have\Nto use it many times more.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.68,0:09:50.23,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The seed is alive. Each time you\Nuse it, its influence increases.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.86,0:09:53.73,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It could eventually unbalance things.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.07,0:09:58.32,dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you're saying you wouldn't use it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.86,0:10:01.87,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could you {\i1}not{\i0} use it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.49,0:10:03.87,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.87,0:10:05.87,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't remember living in a village.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.04,0:10:07.83,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd ditch the land before it could happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.08,0:10:14.51,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our ancestors' bodies lie here in this land, in this soil.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.71,0:10:18.09,dialogue,,0,0,0,,We developed the land and finally\Ngot to where we are now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.09,0:10:20.39,dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is our one single achievement.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.84,0:10:25.18,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't one foul the soil by planting\Nsuch an abomination in it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.52,0:10:33.69,dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.23,0:10:35.69,dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is all just a "what-if".
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.53,0:10:37.86,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.53,0:10:41.53,dialogue,,0,0,0,,If such a seed existed,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.95,0:10:46.75,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd think it over more carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.46,0:10:52.17,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.92,0:10:56.84,dialogue,,0,0,0,,such a seed does exist in the hands of one man.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.84,0:11:06.93,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like the heavy grains of an overripe ear of rice, it\Ninevitably falls from the hands and onto the soil...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.48,0:11:12.94,dialogue,,0,0,0,,not knowing the forthcoming suffering of man.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.24,0:11:22.53,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you done talking?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.37,0:11:25.33,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, mostly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.04,0:11:29.83,dialogue,,0,0,0,,So are you going to help everyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.00,0:11:33.67,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but I need the agreement\Nof everyone in the village,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.04,0:11:36.38,dialogue,,0,0,0,,after I tell them about how the "cursed harvest" works.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.63,0:11:39.38,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can you go gather everyone in one spot?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.13,0:11:43.55,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. But what are you planning?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.68,0:11:46.31,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you suggesting that we burn the farms?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.89,0:11:54.44,dialogue,,0,0,0,,That we have no choice but to destroy the seed\Nbefore the "divine fang" appears in someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.27,0:11:58.36,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right. So you finally admit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.73,0:12:00.44,dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're mistaken.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.82,0:12:03.16,dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're not helping anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.16,0:12:04.95,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you going to make everyone starve?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.41,0:12:07.87,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone just needs to be gone for a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.37,0:12:14.38,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It shouldn't be hard for everyone to disperse\Nand live on their own for a year elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.25,0:12:18.38,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The burned ashes should fertilize the soil in the spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.96,0:12:22.68,dialogue,,0,0,0,,How many people do you think will\Ncome back once they're gone?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.72,0:12:27.10,dialogue,,0,0,0,,People can bear with it because they don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.39,0:12:30.39,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because they don't know what a {\i1}real{\i0} big harvest is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.56,0:12:32.10,dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is how it's supposed to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.98,0:12:38.52,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I won't let you spread any crazy rumors.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.82,0:12:42.82,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saishu-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.49,0:12:50.54,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is the old man ill?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.33,0:12:54.00,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.25,0:12:58.04,dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's been sick these days; been taking medicine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.71,0:12:59.34,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Medicine?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.30,0:13:02.17,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think it's the stuff in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.85,0:13:20.73,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know what you were thinking\Ndrinking such poison,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.11,0:13:24.07,dialogue,,0,0,0,,but don't you think you'd be a bit irresponsible\Nto just let yourself die?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.86,0:13:27.57,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Mushi-shi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.24,0:13:30.03,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Considering you intended to burn the crops,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.03,0:13:34.08,dialogue,,0,0,0,,you must not have come to\Nuse the seed for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.16,0:13:35.96,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.92,0:13:41.75,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've decided that I'd be the last victim of the seed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.80,0:13:51.43,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's been said that the seed was brought back
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.43,0:13:54.18,dialogue,,0,0,0,,from somewhere by the chief mourner two generations ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.02,0:14:00.48,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since then the seed had been used countless\Ntimes each time there was a disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.48,0:14:04.99,dialogue,,0,0,0,,To prevent confusion, only the chief\Nmourner knew of the seed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.99,0:14:13.04,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was twenty years ago that we first had to consider\Nthe use of the seed in my generation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.54,0:14:15.87,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I better use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.58,0:14:17.96,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}At this rate...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.21,0:14:20.96,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm going out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.38,0:14:23.96,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay, take care.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.77,0:14:37.94,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm doing the right thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.52,0:14:40.81,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was thoughtful for the whole village.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.94,0:14:44.48,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This is the right thing to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.28,0:14:49.57,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd never known that my wife was\Nholding anything back from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.74,0:14:56.00,dialogue,,0,0,0,,That autumn, it was my wife that\Npossessed the "divine fang".
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.54,0:15:02.25,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.96,0:15:04.67,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eat the rice.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.88,0:15:07.63,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or you'll die too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.14,0:15:13.18,dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.56,0:15:18.35,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eat it even if it hurts.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.77,0:15:25.36,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think I can bear dying, if you're\Ngoing to be eating my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.07,0:15:28.53,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even such rice,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.24,0:15:32.61,dialogue,,0,0,0,,my body consumed greedily.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.12,0:15:39.96,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Later, I was about to throw out\Nthe seed that fell from my wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.00,0:15:45.04,dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I thought about the inevitable\Narrival of the next disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.21,0:15:47.00,dialogue,,0,0,0,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.59,0:15:52.63,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I realized that I could use the seed just one more\Ntime without seeing anyone becoming a victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.89,0:15:58.60,dialogue,,0,0,0,,And this year, that time has come.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.08,0:16:21.00,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I plan to have Sane dispose of the\Nseed when it falls from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.00,0:16:33.01,notes,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)}Koumyakusuji: koumyaku channel
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.66,0:16:28.05,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I learned that if it is buried in a so-called\N"Koumyakusuji", it'd lose form.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.75,0:16:33.01,dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, I don't intend to explain\Nthe nature of the seed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.39,0:16:35.72,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that really okay with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.30,0:16:41.73,dialogue,,0,0,0,,You must want to live to see this land\Nprosper more than anyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.52,0:16:43.56,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I already can.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.02,0:16:46.44,dialogue,,0,0,0,,So long as we don't give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.40,0:16:50.32,dialogue,,0,0,0,,This land will slowly become richer.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.99,0:16:55.32,dialogue,,0,0,0,,There will eventually be a time when\Nwe can live without worries.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.07,0:16:59.37,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know how many generations it'll take.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.37,0:17:01.66,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't be able to see it with my eyes anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.79,0:17:06.46,dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.21,0:17:09.09,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do what you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.80,0:17:12.63,dialogue,,0,0,0,,One more thing I want to ask you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.08,0:17:44.37,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saishu-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.33,0:17:49.50,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mom's going to be fine now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.50,0:17:52.13,dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's getting better with the rice.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.30,0:17:54.13,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really. I'm glad to hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.51,0:17:55.88,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just like I told you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.13,0:17:56.88,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.09,0:18:01.18,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Sane. I have something I need to tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.43,0:18:05.27,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something really important. Listen carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.77,0:18:12.57,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yo, Sane, your prayers aren't the same as last year's.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.40,0:18:19.24,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, has the "divine fang" shown up on anyone yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.24,0:18:21.37,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nope, haven't heard about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.78,0:18:26.62,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe the harvest this year wasn't cursed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.87,0:18:32.17,dialogue,,0,0,0,,So then this rice must have been\Nthe result of our effort alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.89,0:18:46.39,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.81,0:18:51.86,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The festival's going well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.40,0:18:53.73,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone's having fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.22,0:19:19.22,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.80,0:19:22.68,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll do as you said.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.64,0:19:28.77,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saishu-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.44,0:19:37.99,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why does it have to be this way?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.44,0:19:40.28,dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is just wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.04,0:19:49.16,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell anyone what I'm about to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.92,0:19:54.59,dialogue,,0,0,0,,One more thing I want to ask you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.55,0:20:01.88,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I said the Koumyaku is life itself, but it isn't enough\Nto just pour it into an organism to revive it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.55,0:20:06.56,dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, it's the seed that makes it possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.27,0:20:10.43,dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a gamble.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.68,0:20:13.81,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm willing to bet that if a lifeform eats\Nit, they could come back to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.23,0:20:21.20,dialogue,,0,0,0,,But unlike with the plants, the seed\Nwill no doubt remain in your body.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.07,0:20:26.41,dialogue,,0,0,0,,In which case, you will become an immortal...\N"thing", beyond a lifeform.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.87,0:20:30.41,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would you risk it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.50,0:20:35.71,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wasn't that your most forbidden act?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.84,0:20:40.09,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would you be forgiven for such a thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.96,0:20:43.38,dialogue,,0,0,0,,No one will know if you keep quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.68,0:20:48.85,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know if it'd succeed, and I don't\Nknow if it'd be in your best interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.60,0:20:51.39,dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if you'd like to try it...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.69,0:20:56.73,dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is my apology to you for wrangling out the\Ntruth about the seed from your wounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.69,0:20:59.61,dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a crime I'm willing to commit.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.28,0:21:02.15,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Think it over carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.03,0:21:05.66,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}My answer wouldn't be any different,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.07,0:21:09.70,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}whether I think it over or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.37,0:21:18.50,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'd still like to watch over the land.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.63,0:21:22.30,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'd still like to see what happens to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.02,0:21:42.23,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I want to see if what I did was the right thing to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.91,0:21:57.58,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The abundant harvest of that year would become\Na tale that was passed down for ages.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.04,0:21:59.88,dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the same time,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.09,0:22:04.47,dialogue,,0,0,0,,a strange legend was born.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.47,0:22:11.10,dialogue,,0,0,0,,During the year in which the long lasting\N"cursed harvest" came to an end,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.68,0:22:15.77,dialogue,,0,0,0,,the rice that was produced had revived a dead man.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.48,0:22:22.69,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The man became immortal and walked the lands.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.82,0:22:30.66,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Every so often, he'd come back and bring with\Nhim new techniques to fertilize the land.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.97,0:23:35.51,next-title,,0,0,0,,{\pos(890.286,342.857)\fad(0,2000)\be1}The\NHeavy\NSeed
